# 0G Airdrop Scanner - Cron Configuration Example
#
# Add this to your crontab using: crontab -e
#
# This configuration runs the scanner every 5 hours
# Adjust the path to your project directory

# Run scanner every 5 hours
0 */5 * * * cd /mnt/c/Users/kubas/Desktop/0g-transparency/backend-new && npm run scanner >> /dev/null 2>&1

# Alternative schedules:
# Every 3 hours:     0 */3 * * *
# Every 6 hours:     0 */6 * * *
# Every 12 hours:    0 */12 * * *
# Once daily at 2am: 0 2 * * *
# Twice daily:       0 2,14 * * *

# For testing (every 5 minutes):
# */5 * * * * cd /mnt/c/Users/kubas/Desktop/0g-transparency/backend-new && npm run scanner

# View logs:
# Scanner logs are saved in: backend-new/logs/scanner-YYYY-MM-DD.log

